    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\n[sonarlint.nvim](https://gitlab.com/schrieveslaach/sonarlint.nvim) is a LSP that is based on Java which needs to be started with `java -jar path/to/the/lsp.jar â€¦more optionsâ€¦` and when invoking `:LspInfo` it prints the Java version instead of the version of sonarlint-language-server because `nvim-lspconfig` invokes `java --version` which leads to following output:\n\n```\n- Client: `sonarlint.nvim` (id: 2, bufnr: [1])\n  root directory:    ~/Projekte/Open-Source/sonarlint-language-server/\n  filetypes:         \n  cmd:               /usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk/bin/java -jar ~/.local/share/nvim/mason/packages/sonarlint-language-server/extension/server/sonarlint-ls.jar -stdio -analyzers ~/.local/share/nvim/mason/share/sonarlint-analyzers/csharpenterprise.jar â€¦\n  version:           `openjdk 17.0.13 2024-10-15`\n  executable:        true\n  autostart:         false\n```\n\nThe `--version` flag has been introduced to sonarlint-language-server via https://github.com/SonarSource/sonarlint-language-server/pull/402, succeeded by https://github.com/SonarSource/sonarlint-language-server/pull/410, and `nvim-lspconfig` needs to invoke `java -jar path/to/the/lsp.jar --version`.\n\nDo you think there is a way to make `nvim-lspconfig` aware of such situations?",
    "closed_at": "2025-03-26T19:13:10Z",
